{"questionId":"10125","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1a\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">The function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> can also be written&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = x\\left( {x - 1} \\right)\\left( {rx - s} \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n</math></span> are integers. Find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Factorizing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = x\\left( {2{x^2} - 5x + 3} \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = \\left( {{x^2} - x} \\right)\\left( {rx - s} \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r = 2\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s = 3\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (accept <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = x\\left( {x - 1} \\right)\\left( {2x - 3} \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1A1&nbsp; &nbsp; N3</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10125","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.8e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"The function f can also be written f ( x ) = x ( x − 1 ) ( r x − s ) where r and s are integers. Find r and s .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}